|title=A bold open-access push in Germany could change the future of academic publishing|date=2017-08-23|work=Science {{!}} AAAS|accessdate=2017-08-24|language=en|archive-date=2017-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170824013630/http://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/08/bold-open-access-push-germany-could-change-future-academic-publishing|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hrk.de/press/press-releases/press-release/meldung/researchers-resign-editorship-of-elsevier-journals-4237/|title=Researchers resign editorship of Elsevier journals|last=Conference|first=German Rectors'|accessdate=2017-10-16|language=en|archive-date=2017-10-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171017042346/https://www.hrk.de/press/press-releases/press-release/meldung/researchers-resign-editorship-of-elsevier-journals-4237/|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[物理化学|物理化学家]]Horst Hippler，DEAL联合体的发言人，陈述指“纳税人有权阅读他们为之付出的东西”，且“出版商必须了解，转向价格可负担的[[开放获取|开放获取]]出版，是不可逆的路线”。就该项目的成因，Hippler表示：“能完整、免费——还有更重要的——持续取得发表的科研内容对我们的研究人员来说极为重要……就这方面来看，我们想要和爱思唯尔及其他科研出版社，达成一个公平且有可持续性的合适条款。”<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chemistryworld.com/news/german-universities-take-on-elsevier-/3007807.article|title=German universities take on Elsevier|author=|last=Stafford|first=Ned|date=2017-08-05|work=|newspaper=Chemistry World|accessdate=2018-07-29|language=en|archive-date=2018-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180805234148/https://www.chemistryworld.com/news/german-universities-take-on-elsevier-/3007807.article|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.editage.cn/insights/2211.html|title=德国科研单位推动与爱思唯尔的公平交易，取得付费墙后的研究|author=Sneha Kulkarni|date=2017-09-04|work=|newspaper=意得辑专家视点 Editage Insights|accessdate=2018-07-29|language=zh-hans|archive-date=2018-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180805210240/https://www.editage.cn/insights/2211.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

